definitions.definition: Someone who takes care of a place or thing; someone looking after a place, or responsible for keeping it in good repair.
examples: Her dad was a cemetery caretaker for many years. There was a lot of landscaping work. The gravedigging itself was done with backhoes.

definitions.definition: A caregiver (person who provides care to another).

main_definition: Someone who takes care of a place or thing; someone looking after a place, or responsible for keeping it in good repair.
